<div id="review_99675857" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/99675857" />
    <a title="Christina" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3607633-christina"><img alt="Christina" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1291999719p2/3607633.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/99675857?book_show_action=true">Apr 22, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Christina" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Christina" href="/user/show/3607633-christina">Christina</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780140067774" href="/book/show/952284.Obasan">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer99675857" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4071201697248178212">Obasan is a fascinating look into the lives and experiences of a Japanese-Canadian family from the perspective of an adult family member who was born and raised in Canada. Through this novel, the reader discovers what might be to some a surprising aspect of Canada&apos;s past: our attempt to remove all Asian immigrants from Canada after Japan&apos;s attack on Pearl Harbor.<br/><br/>This is the only book that has ever made me cry. I was genuinely caught off guard by the sheer devastation described in the last few pa</span>
  <span id="freeText4071201697248178212" style="display:none">Obasan is a fascinating look into the lives and experiences of a Japanese-Canadian family from the perspective of an adult family member who was born and raised in Canada. Through this novel, the reader discovers what might be to some a surprising aspect of Canada's past: our attempt to remove all Asian immigrants from Canada after Japan's attack on Pearl Harbor.<br /><br />This is the only book that has ever made me cry. I was genuinely caught off guard by the sheer devastation described in the last few pages of the novel. Juxtaposed with the passive, complacent attitudes depicted throughout the rest of the novel, it completely overwhelmed me. I highly recommend this book.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="4071201697248178212" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


